      "question": "If the $HCF$ of $306$ and $657$ is $9$, find their $LCM$.",
      "answer": "$22338$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the property that for any two positive integers $a$ and $b$, $HCF(a, b) \\times LCM(a, b) = a \\times b$.",
          "Substitute the given values $a = 306$, $b = 657$, and $HCF = 9$ to calculate the $LCM$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$LCM(306, 657) = \\frac{306 \\times 657}{HCF(306, 657)} \\\\ LCM(306, 657) = \\frac{306 \\times 657}{9} \\\\ LCM(306, 657) = 34 \\times 657 = 22338$"
      },
