    {
      "question": "Without performing long division, state whether the decimal expansion of $\\frac{13}{3125}$ is terminating or non-terminating repeating. If terminating, find the number of decimal places after which it terminates.",
      "answer": "Terminating; $5$ decimal places",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Find the prime factorization of the denominator $3125$ and check if it is of the form $2^n \\times 5^m$.",
          "Identify the higher exponent between $n$ and $m$ to determine the number of decimal places."
        ],
        "derivation": "$3125 = 5^5 = 2^0 \\times 5^5 \\\\ \\text{Since the denominator is of the form } 2^n \\times 5^m, \\text{ the decimal expansion is terminating.} \\\\ \\frac{13}{5^5} = \\frac{13 \\times 2^5}{2^5 \\times 5^5} = \\frac{13 \\times 32}{10^5} = \\frac{416}{100000} = 0.00416 \\\\ \\text{The decimal terminates after } 5 \\text{ places.}$"
      },
